# Myth of Rune — project context

You are a senior game developer on **Myth of Rune**: MMORPG 2D top-down, **Godot 4** client + **Node/TypeScript** backend (gateway, login, world, combat), **Zod** in `shared/`, **Redis** + **Postgres**.

## Repo layout (reference)

- `client/` — Godot 4 (`project.godot`); main scene `scenes/main/Main.tscn`; autoloads `GameConfig`, `Session`, `EventBus`, `GameManager`, `InputBootstrap`.
- `shared/src/schemas/` — Zod contracts (source of truth; do not duplicate types).
- `gateway/`, `login-server/`, `world-server/`, `combat-server/` — backend; new HTTP goes through **gateway**.
- `tools/` — Python helpers (e.g. atlas verify); not under `res://`.

## Autoloads (project.godot)

| Name | Script |
|---|-----|
| EventBus | `scripts/autoload/EventBus.gd` |
| GameManager | `scripts/autoload/GameManager.gd` |
| InputBootstrap | `scripts/autoload/InputBootstrap.gd` |
| GameConfig | `autoload/GameConfig.gd` |
| Session | `autoload/Session.gd` |

## Agent collaboration

- **Cursor (architect)**: multi-file refactors, Godot + TS together, cross-service debugging.
- **Deep domain work**: combat formulas, `CharacterSprite` atlas math, Zod propagation, world rooms/broadcast, Python tools.

Flow: map files → sketch architecture → implement per domain (schemas → servers → client) → integrate and verify `MAP_BOUNDS`, autoloads, `res://`.

## Runtime (high level)

`Main` → `Login` (HTTP via gateway) → JWT in `Session` → `World` (WebSocket `GameConfig` → gateway `/ws?token=…`) → local player sends `move`; server sends `state`; HUD via `EventBus`.

## WebSocket contracts (import from `shared/dist` in services)

| Message | Direction | Schema |
|---|-----|-----|
| `move` | client → server | `world.ts` → `MoveMessage` |
| `welcome` | server → client | `world.ts` → `WelcomeMessage` |
| `state` | server → client | `world.ts` → `StateMessage` |
| `combat_event` | server → client | `combat.ts` → `CombatEvent` |

## Checklist before coding

- Read the full file before editing.
- Game assets under `client/assets/`; `res://` resolves inside `client/`.
- New HTTP behind **gateway**; `/login` and `/register` alias to `/auth/*` — no duplicate routes.
- Cross-scene signaling via **EventBus**, not ad-hoc cross-scene references.
- Map **800×600** — align with `MAP_BOUNDS` on world-server for movement/spawn.
- Do not remove existing behavior without explicit confirmation.
- Commits: conventional `type(scope): description` in English.
